        "text": "The combination of both distinctions, system/environment and formal/informal, could be achieved by the term \"membership role\" („Mitgliedschaftsrolle“). Consequently, it forms the central category of the preceding text. For only communications made by the members of the organization in their role as members are attributed to the organization. Everything else, buildings, machines, but also the people themselves and all that non-members negotiate among themselves, belongs to the environment of the system. Moreover, it is clear that membership is assumed by decisions and terminated by decisions. Thus, it is decisions by which the organization generates itself and, in its and demarcates itself from its environment in ongoing communication. Finally, the notion of role was meant to express that while roles establish membership in the organization and certain general expectations, the violation of which will lead to loss of membership in the long run, this still leaves much room for maneuver that can be filled by both formal and informal communication."
