        "text": "One does not have to describe such a zigzag course, which always swings the respective used distinctions along, as progress, as if nothing would be lost. Rather, an evolutionary theory applies to the situation, which reckons with the fact that in the course of time the complexity to be mastered in the system increases. It then becomes more and more difficult to imagine how a comprehensive theory is still possible. Perhaps in much higher degrees of abstraction. Perhaps only in the ecumenical conciliation of a \"postmodern\" discourse. One could then only sail around in the island world of discourse and, with the French philosopher Jean-Franfois Lyotard, view it from a ship."
